00:08:01.970 --> 00:08:05.390
Not squinting, but
just more narrow.

00:08:05.390 --> 00:08:06.680
ADAM GRANT: All right.

00:08:06.680 --> 00:08:08.810
So you feel like the guy on the
right, the taker, is sort

00:08:08.810 --> 00:08:10.624
of looking you right
in the eye?

00:08:10.624 --> 00:08:12.520
AUDIENCE: Yeah, it's like he's
posing for a commercial.

00:08:12.520 --> 00:08:15.000
ADAM GRANT: He's posing
for a commercial.

00:08:15.000 --> 00:08:16.230
Or a press photo shoot.

00:08:16.230 --> 00:08:17.220
Yeah.

00:08:17.220 --> 00:08:19.040
So there's an actual study
by Keith Campbell and his

00:08:19.040 --> 00:08:23.790
colleagues looking at spotting
takers on Facebook.

00:08:23.790 --> 00:08:26.130
They look at the narcissistic
variety of takers, and they

00:08:26.130 --> 00:08:29.310
show that takers actually post
vainer profile pictures of

00:08:29.310 --> 00:08:30.440
themselves.

00:08:30.440 --> 00:08:32.380
They're not necessarily more
attractive human beings in

00:08:32.380 --> 00:08:34.950
general, but you will find a
greater distance between how

00:08:34.950 --> 00:08:37.280
they look every day and how hot
they are in their profile

00:08:37.280 --> 00:08:39.690
photo, because they have
to put that best

00:08:39.690 --> 00:08:41.402
foot forward, right?

00:08:41.402 --> 00:08:41.820
All right.

00:08:41.820 --> 00:08:42.750
So that's one interesting cue.

00:08:42.750 --> 00:08:45.540
What else do you see about the
man on the right that signals

00:08:45.540 --> 00:08:47.540
that man is a taker?

00:08:47.540 --> 00:08:48.200
He's selfish.

00:08:48.200 --> 00:08:49.040
He's egotistical.

00:08:49.040 --> 00:08:50.090
Now no one wants to answer.

00:08:50.090 --> 00:08:51.297
But yes, right here.

00:08:51.297 --> 00:08:53.240
AUDIENCE: I think his smile
looks a little forced.

00:08:53.240 --> 00:08:54.340
ADAM GRANT: The smile
looks forced.

00:08:54.340 --> 00:08:56.240
How so?

00:08:56.240 --> 00:08:57.960
AUDIENCE: It's like tense.

00:08:57.960 --> 00:08:59.700
ADAM GRANT: It's tense.

