00:09:10.900 --> 00:09:12.180
AUDIENCE: [LAUGHTER]

00:09:12.180 --> 00:09:13.160
ADAM GRANT: Any other cues?

00:09:13.160 --> 00:09:16.114
John Carmel, what
about the eyes?

00:09:16.114 --> 00:09:17.030
AUDIENCE: I don't know.

00:09:17.030 --> 00:09:18.600
ADAM GRANT: I know you've
been well trained

00:09:18.600 --> 00:09:19.850
to look at the eyes.

00:09:24.914 --> 00:09:25.902
AUDIENCE: I don't remember.

00:09:25.902 --> 00:09:27.890
ADAM GRANT: Ugh.

00:09:27.890 --> 00:09:30.070
Anybody use the eyes other than
just general kindness?

00:09:30.070 --> 00:09:31.080
A more specific cue?

00:09:31.080 --> 00:09:31.795
Yes.

00:09:31.795 --> 00:09:34.150
AUDIENCE: The guy on the left
looks like he's making direct

00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:37.132
eye contact, the one on the
right looks like he's looking

00:09:37.132 --> 00:09:38.630
a little bit above you.

00:09:38.630 --> 00:09:39.310
ADAM GRANT: Yeah.

00:09:39.310 --> 00:09:39.960
All right.

00:09:39.960 --> 00:09:40.730
That's a possibility.

00:09:40.730 --> 00:09:41.490
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:09:41.490 --> 00:09:41.780
ADAM GRANT: A-ha!

00:09:41.780 --> 00:09:43.886
Bring it on.

00:09:43.886 --> 00:09:46.992
AUDIENCE: It's when you're doing
a fake smile your eyes

00:09:46.992 --> 00:09:49.820
lie because I think they
crinkle right here.

00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:50.630
ADAM GRANT: They
don't crinkle.

00:09:50.630 --> 00:09:50.930
AUDIENCE: Or don't crinkle.

00:09:50.930 --> 00:09:51.560
ADAM GRANT: Yes.

